to the editor re 12th graders national science scores slip news article nov 21 american students do poorly on science performance tests because there are too few teachers prepared in science coming out of teacher training institutions the brightest scientists are still snapped up by industry resulting in a continuing lack of interest in science teaching there needs to be a national policy on support for science education even the well financed national science foundation can not attend to the needs of individual school districts programs supported by the foundation tend to be important experiments in selected schools and districts but they can not be replicated because of the lack of money in most of the other school districts jerrold ross new york nov 21 2001 the writer is dean of the school of education and human services st john 's university

